column5: I talked to bailey about it... My good friends parents are  the old owners....they're going to be furious when they find out.
It was either $18 or $28 in rockland....  Couldn't believe it...  I have 2 free boat launches within minutes of my house.... Love it... And surprisingly... They aren't as busy as the pay ones... Lol

When they raised it to $30 I would have said see ya!!! Anything more than $15 for launch and park is too much. IMHO  Most of the lakes I launch on here are FREE!!!! The ones you have to pay for are in Territorial parks and are cheap. The one lake I fish where I launch and park inside the park is $30 . . . . . . . . . . . FOR THE SEASON!!!!!!!! May to September The rest of the year is free. Double concrete ramp with large docks and plenty of parking.
Wow..  That's brutal.  Who knows the entire story though..  They may be about to go teats up.. Grabbing a straws to pay the bills..?  How much is a parking ticket?  Not Likely more than $45....
Or perhaps the local cottage association has a deal with them....all their repairs and boating needs bought through them and in return they try to inhibit boat traffic on the lake...
